[{"location":"man/#API-documentation","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/#Orthographic-system","page":"API documentation","title":"Orthographic system","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"LycianAscii\nlycianAscii\ncodepoints\ntokentypes","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#Lycian.LycianAscii","page":"API documentation","title":"Lycian.LycianAscii","text":"An orthographic system for encoding the Lycian alphabet primarily using ASCII characaters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"man/#Lycian.lycianAscii","page":"API documentation","title":"Lycian.lycianAscii","text":"Instantiate a LycianAscii with correct code points and token types.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"man/#Orthography.codepoints","page":"API documentation","title":"Orthography.codepoints","text":"Generic function to retrieve list of codepoints for an OrthographicSystem.\n\ncodepoints(ortho)\n\n\n\n\n\n\nImplement codepoints function for SimpleAscii.\n\ncodepoints(ortho)\n\n\n\n\n\n\nImplement Orthography's codepoints functions for LycianAscii.\n\ncodepoints(ortho)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"man/#Orthography.tokentypes","page":"API documentation","title":"Orthography.tokentypes","text":"Generic function to retrieve a list of tokentypes for an OrthographicSystem.\n\n\n\n\n\nImplement tokentypes function for SimpleAscii.\n\ntokentypes(ortho)\n\n\n\n\n\n\nImplement Orthography's tokentypes functions for LycianAscii.\n\ntokentypes(ortho)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"man/#Lexicon","page":"API documentation","title":"Lexicon","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"lexicon_df\nlookuplex","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#Lycian.lexicon_df","page":"API documentation","title":"Lycian.lexicon_df","text":"Construct a DataFrame with Lycian lexicon.\n\nlexicon_df()\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"man/#Lycian.lookuplex","page":"API documentation","title":"Lycian.lookuplex","text":"Lookup entry identified by LexemeUrn in Lycian lexicon.\n\nlookuplex(lexicon, lexu)\n\n\n\n\n\n\nLookup entry identified by Cite2Urn in Lycian lexicon.\n\nlookuplex(lexicon, u)\n\n\n\n\n\n\nLookup entry identified by URN string in Lycian lexicon.\n\nlookuplex(lexicon, urnstring)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"man/#Morphology","page":"API documentation","title":"Morphology","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/","page":"API documentation","title":"API documentation","text":"morph_df\nlookupmorph\nparsetoken","category":"page"},{"location":"man/#Lycian.morph_df","page":"API documentation","title":"Lycian.morph_df","text":"Construct a DataFrame with Lycian morphology.\n\nmorph_df()\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"guide/analysis/#A-more-complex-example","page":"A more complex example","title":"A more complex example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/analysis/","page":"A more complex example","title":"A more complex example","text":"TBA:","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/analysis/","page":"A more complex example","title":"A more complex example","text":"you can retrieve a corpus of Lycian texts from Dane Scott's public repository\nyou can select texts and text passges by URN\nyou can create a tokenized edition\nyou can morphologically parse tokens, passages or whole corpora","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/morphology/#User's-guide:-morphology","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"User's guide: morphology","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/morphology/","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"User's guide: morphology","text":"The LycianParser class implements the CitableParser interface.  You can instantiate a LycianParser with the parser() function.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/morphology/","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"User's guide: morphology","text":"using Lycian\nlycianparser = parser()\ntypeof(lycianparser) |> supertype\n\n# output\n\nCitableParser","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/morphology/","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"User's guide: morphology","text":"warning: Prerequisite\nCreating a parser downloads a dataset over the internet into a DataFrame.  If you are not online, you will have to manually create a parser by constructing a DataFrame from a local copy of the data set at https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Descot21/Lycian/master/morphology/analyses.cex","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/morphology/#Parsing-strings","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"Parsing strings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/morphology/","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"User's guide: morphology","text":"The most efficient way to parse a string value for a single token is to provide three parameters to the parsetoken function: the parser, the string value, and the data set that the parser has already downloaded.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/morphology/","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"User's guide: morphology","text":"The parser comes up with only one analysis for the form tideimis.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/morphology/","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"User's guide: morphology","text":"parses = parsetoken(lycianparser, \"tideimis\", lycianparser.data)\nlength(parses)\n\n# output\n\n1","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/morphology/#The-lexicon","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"The lexicon","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/morphology/#The-morphological-database","page":"User's guide: morphology","title":"The morphological database","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Lycian.jl-Documentation","page":"Home","title":"Lycian.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = Lycian","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Lycian.jl supports working with a digital corpus of Lycian texts.  It allows you to:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"validate the orthography of a text, and convert between an ASCII-based orthography and the Lycian range of Unicode.\ntokenize text in Lycian using the MID Orthography interface for parsing texts into classified tokens\nanalyze the morphology of lexical tokens using the CitableParserBuilder module.  Analyses identify lexemes and forms with URN values that can be used to look up entries in a Lycian lexicon, and a Lycian morphological database, respectively.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/orthography/#User's-guide:-orthography","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"User's guide: orthography","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/orthography/#Trancoding-Lycian","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"Trancoding Lycian","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/orthography/","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"User's guide: orthography","text":"The ucode function transcodes from ASCII to Unicode in the Lycian range.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/orthography/","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"User's guide: orthography","text":"using Lycian\nLycian.ucode(\"prNnawatE\") \n\n# output\n\n\"ðŠ“ðŠ•ðŠ‘ðŠðŠ€ðŠ‡ðŠ€ðŠ—ðŠš\"","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/orthography/#Validating-orthography","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"Validating orthography","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/orthography/","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"User's guide: orthography","text":"The LycianAscii type implements the OrthographicSystem abstraction.  You can create an instance with the lycianAscii() function","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/orthography/","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"User's guide: orthography","text":"using Lycian\northography = lycianAscii()\ntypeof(orthography) |> supertype\n\n# output\n\nOrthography.OrthographicSystem","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/orthography/","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"User's guide: orthography","text":"Validate orthography:","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/orthography/","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"User's guide: orthography","text":"using Orthography\nvalidstring(orthography, \"prNnawatE\")\n\n# output\n\ntrue","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/orthography/","page":"User's guide: orthography","title":"User's guide: orthography","text":"validstring(orthography,\"Lycian!\")\n\n# output\n\nfalse","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/tokenization/#User's-guide:-tokenization","page":"User's guide: tokenization","title":"User's guide: tokenization","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"guide/tokenization/","page":"User's guide: tokenization","title":"User's guide: tokenization","text":"The Orthography module also defines a tokenize function.","category":"page"},{"location":"guide/tokenization/","page":"User's guide: tokenization","title":"User's guide: tokenization","text":"using Orthography\nusing Lycian\northo  = lycianAscii()\ntokens = tokenize(ortho, \"ebENnE : xopA : mE=ti prNnawatE\")\ntokens\n\n# output\n\n7-element Vector{OrthographicToken}:\n OrthographicToken(\"ebENnE\", LexicalToken())\n OrthographicToken(\":\", PunctuationToken())\n OrthographicToken(\"xopA\", LexicalToken())\n OrthographicToken(\":\", PunctuationToken())\n OrthographicToken(\"mE\", LexicalToken())\n OrthographicToken(\"ti\", LexicalToken())\n OrthographicToken(\"prNnawatE\", LexicalToken())","category":"page"}]
